cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT 

The paper discusses techniques for efficient random sampling of combinatorial structures, which is a topic that falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The use of generating functions and enumeration sequences also suggests a connection to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The mention of families of objects and the need for uniformity among objects of each size suggests a connection to Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT).
